	"keywords": "Design, UI, UX, Technology, Programming",
	"description": "Life can be tough sometimes for UI designers. While they get to create great\ndesigns, they also get to deal with pressure from clients or PMs. They’re\nrequired to consider user experience and user flow. And they often struggle to\nfind an effective way to communicate with developers.\n\nTo relieve some of the pressure from my fellow designers, I want to help by\nintroducing a better way of handling UI components with state variations. I\nbelieve this is one of the biggest challenges designers face.\n\n",
	"headline": "How to design UI states and communicate with developers using FSM table",
